msgctxt "user_friendly_privacy_policy_helptext"
msgid ""
"BMW had few links to various privacy policies than other car companies we reviewed. However, their privacy notices were still long, complicated, and full of legalese that was often difficult to "
"follow and understand clearly."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "uses_encryption_helptext"
msgid ""
"BMW say, \"Collected data is transferred only in encrypted form. Sensitive data is also saved only in encrypted form.\" \r"
"<br/> <br/>However, we cannot determine if all data sitting on the car, including telematic data the car collects as well as data shared when you connect your phone sits encrypted, and if all collected data is encrypted in transit. We reached out to the company to attempt to determine this multiple times and received no response."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "security_updates_helptext"
msgid "\"We periodically release software updates so the vehicle has the latest compatible SYNC version.\""
msgstr ""

msgctxt "strong_password_helptext"
msgid ""
"All personal information stored in your online My BMW profile requires a unique password and Login ID to access it (your BMW Login). With this password you can edit, delete or add to information you"
" have shared while visiting our Sites."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "privacy_policy_helptext"
msgid ""
"BMW runs a bug bounty at HackerOne. Not only that, BMW has a section on their website recognizing and thanking security researchers who have helped them identify security issues. Not gonna lie, "
"that's pretty good. Good work BMW."
msgstr ""

